There was no lack of new outfits in 2022…take a look back at some of my personal favs of the year 👗

#fashion #stylist #outfitinspiration #fashioninspo #2022 #throwback

2022, lots of highs and lows as always. The highs were some of the best highs though I could’ve imagined. Here are a few updates: 
1. Daniel & I have lived together for a whole year 
2. I got to welcome my nephew into the world and he has done nothing but bring me more joy daily, even if sadly it’s from afar
3. I had emergency surgery on my appendix, which took me out for about a month and the recovery was not my friend (that was a low to be clear lol)/but Daniel and my friends were such amazing caretakers 
4. This is a big one career wise…I got signed with an agency for Styling!!! If any of you know this industry, it’s a hard, long path of rollercoasters/discouragement/but can have such great outcomes if you really work your a** off. I am so proud to be able to say I now have an agency who believes in me and helping to support me in my goals! 
4. I have witnessed some of the highest highs and lowest lows in my best friends lives lives this year, but through all of it have also witnessed the support systems I am so luckily to be apart of. My friends really know how to show up when it counts. 
5. Lastly, I got to finish the year out with my family and then showing Daniel around my favorite city. I couldn’t have asked for a better wrap to the year.

All in all, this year has been a continual year of growth, laughs, cries and hope. I cannot wait for 2023 and to see what new milestones are right around the corner 🤍

#goodbye2022 #hello2023 #holidays #travels #love #life #family

social_posts.post_text:
I stopped in to see @drchiubhps yesterday. If you’re looking for a place in LA for some cosmetic touchups 💉 this is the place. I’ve had good and bad experiences over the years with different Doctors and this was one of the best. Dr Chiu had an extremely calming demeanor, was also very funny, but most importantly very informative. I like to be well educated and informed in anything I’m doing and he was happy to sit and talk through my questions. 10/10 would visit BHPS again.
